articles.author: ScienceAlert
articles.title: Extreme Fasting: What Does 'One Meal a Day' Actually Do to Your Body?
articles.description: Celebrities have popularized all sorts of outlandish diet trends over the years. One of the latest trends among celebrities is the 'one meal a day' diet (or 'OMAD'). Fans of OMAD include Bruce Springsteen and Coldplay frontman Chris Martin. Many proponents of OMAD claim it helps them better manage their weight and keep fit.

articles.author: 9News
articles.title: 'Highly mutated' COVID-19 variant Pirola has arrived in Australia
articles.description: The first case of the﻿ 'highly mutated' COVID-19 variant BA.2.86, colloquially known as Pirola, has been detected in Australia. Western Australia's health department has confirmed to 9news.com.au it has conducted genomic sequencing on a local case which shows it is 'without significant differences' to BA.2.86 variants found overseas that have sparked global concern.

articles.author: News.com.au
articles.title: Lorde’s heartbreaking news in rare update
articles.description: New Zealand singer Lorde has shared a rare open letter with fans detailing her private struggle in recent months. The incredibly private pop star, 26, revealed she was currently living in London, where she was feeling homesick and 'living with heartbreak again' in a lengthy statement seen by NZ Herald.

articles.author: ABC News
articles.title: Australia signs on to United Nations' High Seas Treaty to give world's oceans protection from pollution, environmental damage
articles.description: Australia has signed a landmark treaty to give two-thirds of the world's oceans a 'fighting chance' at surviving over-fishing and pollution. The United Nations' High Seas Treaty is designed to extend environmental protections to oceans not officially owned by any country.

articles.author: The Motley Fool Australia
articles.title: The Federal Reserve just kept interest rates on hold. So why is the ASX 200 slumping?
articles.description: The US Federal Reserve opted to keep interest rates on hold yesterday (overnight Aussie time). With the Fed taking a pass on an interest rate hike following the latest Federal Open Market Committee (FOMC) meeting, the official funds rate in the United States remains in the 5.25% to 5.50% range.
